[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797326992&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837797326992&q=raw">body</a>]</b>


My problem is the following:

We have some subnets for different institutes. I wan't to give them
the full authority for their own domains. That's no problem for
the normal name to address mapping. But how should I do it for the
inverse mapping?

This is the sittuation:

129.187.187.[1-63]  are the addresses for e16.physik.tu-muenchen.de
129.187.187.[64-127] are the addresses for e20.physik.tu-muenchen.de

I have the authority for 187.187.129.in-addr.arpa, how can I delegate
the authority for the [64-127] bunch of addresses ?

Any suggestions are welcome.

Sincerely,
Klaus Steinberger

